djmaus installation notes

Should work on mac, linux, windows.

1. Install matlab.
2. Install psych toolbox. Download from www.psychtoolbox.org 
3. Install Open Ephys GUI. Download from http://www.open-ephys.org/gui/
4. Install zeroMQ. Download from http://zeromq.org/intro:get-the-software
	alternatively on linux, 
		sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/zeromq
		sudo apt-get update
		sudo apt-get install libzmq3-dbg libzmq3-dev libzmq3
	alternatively on mac, (using brew, available from brew.sh)
		brew install zeromq
		sudo mkdir /opt/local
		sudo mkdir /opt/local/lib
		sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libzmq.dylib  /opt/local/lib/libzmq.dylib 
		sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libzmq.a  /opt/local/lib/libzmq.a
		sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libzmq.la  /opt/local/lib/libzmq.la
		sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libzmq.5.dylib  /opt/local/lib/libzmq.3.dylib 

https://guide.macports.org/#installing.macports
sudo port install zmq3

5. If the zeroMQ mex file doesnâ€™t work (check with matlab_zeroMQ_wrapper_example.m), you might need to compile the source code. 
	Make sure g++ 4.7 is installed:
		sudo apt-get install g++-4.7
		sudo ln -s /usr/bin/g++-4.7 /usr/bin/g++ 
	Download the open-ephys source code from https://github.com/open-ephys/GUI
	Edit GUI/Resources/matlab/compile_matlab_wrapper.m to have the right paths to your OE install, and then run it. Test by running matlab_wrapper

launch GUI
network events source doesn't show? do this:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/zeromq
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install libzmq3-dbg libzmq3-dev libzmq3
(from https://open-ephys.atlassian.net/wiki/display/OEW/Linux)

Network Events documentation: https://open-ephys.atlassian.net/wiki/display/OEW/Network+Events

the python network console might be helpful for development
it requires 
apt-get install python-zmq

installing zeroMQ on mac:
brew install zeromq
this puts it into /usr/local/lib
